{
    "text": "\ud83d\udd18The Hanging Temple\ud83d\udd18 \u26abLocated in Datong City, Shanxi Province, China. \u26abThe Hanging Temple is one of the main tourist attractions and historical sites in the Datong area. \u26abAccording to legend, construction of the temple started at the end of the Northern Wei dynasty (386-534) AD by only one man, a monk named Liaoran and was restored in the 1900th. \u26abThe entire 40 halls and pavilions are all built on cliffs which are over 30 metres (98 ft) from the ground. \u26abInterestingly, the temple is dedicated to not just one religion, but three, with Confucianism, Taoism, and Buddhism all practised within the temple and represented in 78 statues and carvings throughout the temple.  \ud83d\udc49Follow me @ancient.scientist to enjoy more and more posts about our world's marvellous History.\u2764  \ud83d\udce2Dm me for Promotion/ Business/ Advertisement\ud83d\udce9  \ud83d\udcf8I don't own any of these photos and I give all credit to the respective owners. #temple #hangingtempledatong #china #guizhou #hangingtemple #cave #statue #divinities #sculpture #sanctuary #stones #bestplaces #ancientart #ancientworld #explore #explorepage #arqueologia #travelling #archaeology #archeology #heritage #worldheritage #culture #history #heritagesite #commagene #ancientcity",
